Author:
Vol / Page:  83
Edition:
Quote:  Chloromycetin solution injected daily for four days into the udder of a ewe suffering from 'black udder', an acute mastitis, is reported to have produced rapid improvement in the general symptoms .. This is only of academic importance, as 'black udder' seldom affects more than a few ewes.
